            <bug_when>2011-03-16 13:39:07 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Both events (&quot;loaded&quot; and &quot;loadingFailed&quot;) are only avaiable for externally 
loaded images. Adding these events to the image widget is not applicable 
because it is not possible to support this throughout the whole stack down to 
the browser.

It might happen that an image widget is rendered as DIV element with a 
background-image property applied. In this case the browser is not able to 
signal that the image is loaded or the loading failed. This technical issue is 
the reason for not implementing this feature.

Updated the documentation with revision 25715 to better describe the events.</thetext>
